1. Quanquam haec. It is a great missortune that we want the assistance of Donatus in explaining this play. He has either left us no com- mentary upon it, or, what is more likely, his remarks are now lost. In him we often find the true reading, which had been defaced by time, or perverted by transcribers. In this play we have no helps but what have been collected from ancient manuscripts.
